Boil a full #kettle{}.

While it boils, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @chicken breast{260%g}(diced) and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.
> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken cooks, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Zest and halve the @lime{½}.

Once the water has boiled, pour into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{¼%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back into the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and
leave to the side until ready to serve.

Once the chicken is cooked, stir in the garlic, @ginger puree{1%tsp} and
@tomato puree{30%g}. Cook for ~{1%min}.

Pour in the @coconut milk{200%ml}, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @water{75%ml} and
@sugar{1%tsp} for the sauce, then stir together.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until the sauce has thickened,
~{4-5%mins}.

Once thickened, stir in the @baby spinach{100%g} into the stew a handful at a time
until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Remove from the heat, squeeze in some of the lime juice and stir in the
@soy sauce{15%ml}.

Taste and add more lime if needed and add a splash more water if it's a bit too
thick.

Share the rice between your #bowls{} and spoon the chicken stew on top.

Finish with a sprinkling of lime zest and @red chilli flakes{}. Enjoy!

== With King Prawns ==

If you've chosen to add @king prawns{150%g} to your meal, simmer the stew for
~{2%mins}, then bring back to the boil. Stir in the prawns and cook for the
remaining ~{2-3%mins}, then continue as instructed.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. The prawns
> are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.